events.text: Hey, I’m feeling a little nervous about this date I’m going on, is there anything you have that could help out with that?

events.question: Oh yeah, for sure! What kind of stuff are you into?

events.text: A rock fan… Hm… you ever heard of the Stone Smashers?
Hmm, not really. What’s their music like?

Oh, so good. They’re like one of the best rock bands to ever exist.
They’ve got this amazing vocalist that’s able to add this growl to his voice. Adds a nice texture to the music.
I think he used to play drums for another band too…
That sounds interesting! I’ll take a listen.
Wow, I feel so pumped! All it took was that one song too, what was it called again?
Let me see… It’s called “Crow Bar!” It’s on their album, “The Cutter and the Plate!”
Cool, I’ll check it out again sometime! Thanks for pumping me up!
Alright, we got some R&B tracks here… Ooh, do you like the group, “H2OH?”
Hmm, I don’t think I’ve heard of them before. What are they like?

I think they’re one of the best-selling girl groups in the world, pretty impressive.
They’ve got some really good, chill beats. Wanna take a listen?
Wow, I don’t feel so nervous anymore. Like, I feel super confident now! What was the song called, again?
Oh right, she was like “No, I don’t want no suds, a sud is a bubble that makes me unhealthy…” Cool, thanks for the song!
